pdbx_vrpt_summary.trans_nsc: The analyses of the Patterson function reveals a significant off-origin peak that is 45.67 % of the origin peak, indicating pseudo-translational symmetry.  The chance of finding a peak of this or larger height by random in a structure without pseudo-translational symmetry is equal to 1.2779e-04. The detected translational NCS is most likely also responsible for the elevated intensity ratio.  See the relevant section of the logfile for more details.
